Package: unmixR
Title: Latent Class and Profile Analysis via Mixture Modelling
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Pablo D.", "Valencia",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "pabvalenciam@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6809-1805"))
Description: Provides a unified interface for person-centred mixture modelling,
    including Latent Class Analysis (LCA) and Latent Profile Analysis (LPA).
    Supports binary, categorical, and continuous indicator variables, as well
    as mixed measurement models combining different variable types. Structural
    models include multinomial logistic regression for covariate effects on
    class membership, and several distal outcome specifications (continuous
    means, continuous regression, and categorical outcomes with pooled or
    class-specific effects). Models can be estimated using 1-step, 2-step, or
    3-step approaches; the 3-step estimator supports BCH and Maximum Likelihood
    bias corrections. Additional tools include model selection across a range
    of class solutions (AIC, BIC, SABIC, entropy), a Bootstrap Likelihood Ratio
    Test (BLRT) for comparing nested models, analytical and bootstrap Wald
    tests for covariate effects, and bootstrap confidence intervals for odds
    ratios. All methods are implemented in pure base R with no external
    dependencies.
